{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1464206784,"nonce":"ART82ffbLp6qNc1QePH9TDQk0Hs=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIyMTY5MTA3OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/680#issuecomment-221691078"},"message":"\u003e It is an option that we I am using currently. One benefit that we have is that our lab has a dedicated fibre connection to NCBI, we want to max out of connection whenever we can.\n\nHmm, we get 11.5 MBytes/s (very close to the 100MBit/s link that we have) from the NCBI to our lab in Paris, and for us dumping the reads takes more time than downloading. Have you opened the appropriate ports in your firewall and are you sure ascp is not falling back to HTTP transfer mode? have you tested whether you can increase the speed by downloading multiple files at once?\n\nI would obviously be happy about parallelizing the sratools ~~even more~~ , but I'm not sure you will get the desired results that way.","files":null}]}